title: Putting thoughts together
body:
What Bran needs us to know, and what can wait until later:

Bran says Jon needs to know his true circumstances of birth. Now, not later. He doesn’t seem to care about anyone else knowing Jon is the true heir to the IT, but he should assume that once Jon knows, it won’t be long before he tells Dany. Especially if Jon is hearing it from Sam, and Bran isn’t there to control the conversation. Which means Jon needs to know right now, and it’s okay if Dany also finds out she’s not the rightful queen. 

And all this needs to happen now. Before they fight off the snow zombies. Can’t wait to see who survives the winter; got to get Jon up to speed right-the-fuck-now. 

We should be wondering why this is a priority on this timeline. 

Meanwhile, Bran sits out all night waiting for Jaime’s lonely ass to ride through the gates. If Bran knows to expect Jaime in that time frame, he should also know the Lannister army isn’t coming. And he knows that, but he isn’t telling his family about Cersei’s betrayal. Not that it would be a surprise to Sansa, but surely Dany and Tyrion and Jon and Varys and so forth would like to hear it for certain, in as many words, before they get too far into battle plans. But somehow, that much can wait until after Jaime’s arrival.

Bran is super-eager to be the first one to interact with Jaime when he shows up, and sure I can imagine why that is, but I don’t believe it’s JUST because Jaime owes Bran a tremendous apology. I think Bran’s got something a bit bigger in mind for our one-handed knight.

For some reason, in Bran’s mind, Jon knowing the truth of his identity is more urgent than the alliance learning of Cersei’s betrayal. I don’t know to what extent the two deadlines are related, but they are both significant unto themselves. 

I think the reason why Bran feels Jon needs to know about his circumstances of birth right-freaking-now, rather than after they’ve saved the world, is that saving the world depends on Jon knowing he’s ahead of Dany in the line of succession. 

Meanwhile, of course the Northern court need to know, in as many words, that Cersei pulled a fast one on them, but that can wait until Jaime is there to break the news himself. And there’s Bran, making sure to be the first one to see Jaime into the castle. 

It feels like Bran needs to drive a wedge between Jon and Dany, while also knocking Dany several pegs down. And maybe, just maybe, Jaime is part of his plan.

summary: So I think the theory about Bran being the Night King is a solid theory. It would explain why the Night King can always see Bran...
body:
So I think the theory about Bran being the Night King is a solid theory. It would explain why the Night King can always see Bran when he’s pulling some three eyed raven shit on him. Buttttt if Bran is the Night King then the whole Targaryens are the only ones that can ride dragons thing doesn’t apply to dead dragons that are resurrected.

If it still applies then the Night King is a Targaryen. Idk. Thoughts?
